The paper proposes a novel approach for automatic channel pruning of neural networks, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The approach involves training a meta network (meta learning), which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of evolutionary procedures, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CL.
